reviews.text: This is my home base library! Beautiful building and lots of great places to sit down and work! I get in my ZONE here!
Very helpful if they don't have it they will find it
Very historical and beautiful!
This is the best public library in Ellsworth.
Great staff and comfortable environment
Brought my 10 year old. Very educational she loved to see all this birds! Many kinds of owls. Very nice and easy walking trails. Gift shop and restrooms on sight. Wonderful experience.

I decided to visit the sanctuary while my car was being worked on. Best decision I made. There was still snow on the ground so trails would have been slippery for hiking. I was greeted by the caretaker and he kindly showed me around the area viewing a few birds in rehabilitation with. Its stories. Beautiful area and will return when the weather is warmer. A great place to volunteer for a non profit organization.  Thank you for your kindness Mr. Richmond.
Have been visiting the bird sanctuary since the late 1980s. Always a fascinating place.

reviews.author_name: Kathy Giddings New & Used Vehicle Sales Gal
reviews.text: There is a goose there that I love.  Poor baby I'm glad he has a safe home. Don't forget to drop a donation in the box to help out.
This place has great hiking trails. It also provides a good service helping take care of birds that can't re-enter the wild.
Classic downeast comfort food.  You can't go wrong here.  Speedy & tidy diner.
I had the club sandwich very filling reasonable price great service.
Cheap and good!! I had the scorcher!! A must try if you like spicy food

The food was great and priced great as well.  Unfortunately we had what I would call a sub par server.  Never offered to fill up coffees, or offer us any water so we had nothing to drink with our food until I asked.  I don't think this is a reflection on Sylvia's though as all the other servers seemed to be on top of their game.  Just bad luck on our part. Definitely worth a shot.
Always a friendly smile and a decent meal

Absolutely the best lobster dinner have had from PEI down to Maine. Delicious with perfectly prepared lobster and very nice mussels and clams. Very good value with excellent service. Definitely arrive early if you can. Gets busy after 530 but worth the wait.

This place is great! Amazing food and beverage selection. We arrived and had a wait to be seated, so we enjoyed drinks by the water. Really relaxed environment and great desserts to cap off the evening. I wish we had a place like this where I live. I hope to come back and eat there again soon!

My wife and I were staying at Bar Harbor for a week. We took a chance and drove here for a great lobster. It was the best decision and worth the drive. Huge lobster and delicious food. Blueberry pie was to die for. Friendly staff and great view.

Union River Lobster Pot is  a place you don't want to miss. And go hungry, cause you need the room. Wow, they do a grand job taking your order and preparing your meal. For appetizers we ordered the Artichoke Dip, Skewered Shrimp & Scallops, and Fresh Mussels. For the main dinner we had Baked Crab Stuffed Halibut and the Surf & Turf. 

We were all very full from all the awesome food, so we decided the dessert was something we should experience, but had to make it a To Go box. Since it is blueberry season here in Maine, we had to get one of each of their blueberry desserts. The first is the Open Blue Pie, which is a pie crust packed high with fresh blueberries. The other is  the traditional style pie, but man it looks baked to perfection. Well have to wait till tomorrow to dig into them.  I can hardly wait.
Wonderful food. The lobster was exactly right, yummy coleslaw and fabulous blueberry pie.  Great spot, had about a 15 minute wait but well worth it.  Highly recommend.
Everything is so good! I love that you can buy slices so you can try a few different ones! The Bianca is AMAZING

I hate to write a bad review and rarely do it but felt I had to this time. Stopped in on Saturday based on good reviews on google. Ordered an 18 inch and it was dry, like no sauce under the cheese, thin as in paper thin and burnt. It was cracking like glass. The heavy set guy at the counter was slow and unfriendly. I was disappointed enough to say I will never eat there again which is too bad because I really wanted to find a pizza restaurant I liked.
Owner is very rude. Thinks he is some Mafia guy. Pizza sits under heat lamps all day, then heated up, taste like paste. Never will return!!
Best pizza place in maine.....staff is the best

For the money spent, this was the best pizza I had during our month of travelling throughout Maine.  We fed 5 of us off their 18" pie, which was good sauce, cheese, and crust.  Everything tasted fresh.  The guys behind the counter are a little rough, but know what they are doing and keep the place jumping.  Great beer selection as well.
Had a lobster roll and crab roll both where excellent. We also had some of the best onion rings ever. All most worth the trip just for the onion rings.
It was fabulous and chatting with George about everything under the sun made it even better💗

This is my favorite restaurant in the Bar Harbor area. It’s worth the trip off the island. Price is great, cost is reasonable, dining area outside is perfection! They are run efficiently. Don’t let the line run you off. It’s a very good indicator of the quality of food you are going to get. They move along quickly, and your food will be fresh and amazing. I have had all of their seafood and fish and never had a complaint. I can’t give more than 5 stars or I would!
Is not what it used to be before .. common mistakes are made..
Great ice cream. Surprised to find so many items in this place. Will definitely go back for lunch.

I'd have to give more than five stars just for the service. The owner and her daughter were extraordinarily accommodating. I had a hard time enjoying their version of pad Thai. I'm not sure if it's me or the food itself. However, the kitchen and server more than made up for it. i ate their curry instead. The rest of the food was great.

Awesome Thai food each individual dish cook to customers preferences. All the dishes have its own unique taste and flavor. I highly recommend you try all of their dishes if possible.The atmosphere and setting will take your breath away .Original family own since it first open in the early 1990's and still running strong.

Both superlative and lousy, one experience of each in our two visits from afar.  Summer-- lobster stew special was supreme, generous, great side dishes left us eager to return.   Winter-- seafood soup inedibly  salty and not flavorful but generous seafood content.  Pad Thai bizarre with possible bottled sauce? No texture and repellent taste- not a dish anyone had ever messed up in our history.  Promised vegetable addition was missing from dishes.  Has ownership changed?

What was once a reliable restaurant has now become a half hazard excuse for a business, much less eaterie. The hours of operation are sporadic,  closing down for periodic emergencies. When we ordered take out we were told to arrive at a specific time. We drove in late to give them extra time, but when we arrived we were told that our order would be a half hour or more, and the poor waitress looked stressed out. There was no one in the restaurant but one poor guy who was told the same thing and ordered another beer. In short, the place looks more like a pathetic storefront for a nature photographer and jewelry maker than a bonafide restaurant. It is a ghost of its former self. Time to give up the ghost. Terrible excuse for a restaurant 
.

Stood in lobby/reception/photography studio/eBay store waiting to be seated until we got sick of that. Went to the bar to ask if we were waiting in the right place and was greeted by a miserable slob that hated her job. She then told us that the table that was practically in the vestibule was "all she had" even though the actual restaurant of this multiuse building was unavailable. We left (and I told her) because "she sucks".
If this THING is an owner that's sad, if not should be fired.
This is my favorite restaurant in Ellsworth. The chef Ken is absolutely amazing from plating to his intricacies of pouring his soul into your meal. Shinbashi is a must!
Absolutely INCREDIBLE food and clean environment. Inventive food. Love the lobster sushi tacos. Love all the food here! Nice seating and interior. Perfect for a date or friends.
Good dine in experience, sushi is fresh, I've not had good luck with ordering out but i would definitely recommend dining in on weekends
It is what you would expect. Gets the job done and has some food worth eating and has some food worth keeping in text format on the menu.... You will find what is good and what should be left as is.
Good sushi! Special rolls are expensive but some are huge so it feels like an okay value.
